content.article_body: ISLAMABAD, Jan 11 (APP): Big upset was witnessed in the elections of Bhakkar District Bar Association after Malik Mujtaba Yasin of Khichi group won the seat of president securing 248 votes The runner-up candidate of opposition party Sheikh group Malik Zulfiqar Ali Jhamat got 231 votes. The joint candidate of DLG and Sheikh group Sheikh Muhammad Shahid was elected General Secretary by securing 310 votes. Khichi groupas Rana Muhammad Tufail stood at second number after getting 162 votes.
content.summary: Big upset in Bhakkar district bar elections as Khichi group wins president's seat, Malik Zulfiqar Ali Jhamat of Sheikh group gets 231 votes.
